ResourceHeader.ResourceName: SOLO Solar Wind Analyzer, Heavy Ion Sensor (SWA-HIS) Rates, Level 2 (L2), Data

RevisionEvent.Note: Initial release of metadata, ADAPT generated, LFB

ResourceHeader.Description: Rate data for HIS instrument in physical units. Some corrections for instrument characteristics and measurement techniques have been applied. Per Data Product Description Document, efficiency corrections have not been applied. Counts of unclassified ion event words on the HIS detectors (start MCP, stop MCP, SSD) as a function of E/q, integrated over incident angles, TOF and Energy. Includes full counts of events subject to decimation. Rates also include two coincidence rates, the number of events with a valid TOF and energy (triple coincidence), and a count of those with only a valid TOF (double coincidence). These rates are primarily used to evaluate the performance of the instrument, rather than for science. In particular, they can be used for calculation of ion detection efficiency in-flight [von Steiger et al., 2000]. The resolution of this data product can be 30s or 300s. In Burst mode the resolution can be 4s but this can only be run on average 1% of the time due to telemetry constraints. Usage notes can be found via the SWA DOI at https://doi.org/10.5270/esa-ahypgn6.
ResourceHeader.Acknowledgement: Please acknowledge Chris J. Owen (SWA PI -- UCL MSSL) & Stefano Livi (HIS PI -- SwRI). NASA Contract NNG10EK25C.. These Level 2 data require substantial processing for most applications. Users are encouraged to use Level 3 data, which provide the most relevant data products for scientific research. See Data Product Description Document for more information. Contact SWA/HIS team for more information as needed.

Parameter.Name: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: * Time in nanoseconds since January 1, 2000, 12:00:00.000. Converted using time correlation SCET via SPICE time kernel provided by the mission. Currently set to start of accumulation interval. This Parameter exhibits an increasing Monotonic Progression

Parameter.Name: SCET
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Mission elapsed time in spacecraft clock ticks. Note: These are effected by environmental conditions and do not match Earth-based seconds. Beginning of accumulation.

Parameter.Name: ACCUM_SECONDS
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Accumulation time in seconds for each E/q and elevation step

Parameter.Name: QUALITY_FLAG
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: 0=good, 1=caution, 2=bad

Parameter.Name: QUALITY_BITMASK
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Not yet fully implemented. 0:No Issue, 1:Proton Avoidance Triggered, 2:No PHAs Telemetered in Range (range 6/7 prior to Auguest 2020), 4:Elevation Step(s) not represented, 8:Saturation of Input Buffer, 16: Buffer Over Ran.

Parameter.Name: MODE
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Description: Mode. 0: Normal Science, 1: Burst 1, 2: Burst 2, 3: Low Cadence.
Parameter.Caveats: Normal: Full E/q range in nominal 30 sec scan, Burst1: E/q range optimized for slower solar wind in nominal 4 sec scan, Burst2: E/q range optimized for faster solar wind in nominal 4 sec scan, Low Cadence: Full E/q range in nominal 300 sec scan.

Parameter.Name: COMPRESSION_CODE
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Compression code bitmask. 0 = Lossy A, 1 = Lossy C. Bits: 0:SSD, 1:Priorities, 2:Starts, 3:Stops, 4:Double Coincidence, 5:Triple Coincidence, 6:Low TOF, 7:Alpha Decimation, 8:Proton Decimation, 9:Position A Singles, 10:Position B Singles.

Parameter.Name: STEP_TABLE
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Science Configuration Packet's HV Sweep Scan Control Table Identification Number

Parameter.Name: MAIN_ENABLES
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Bitmask for enabled rates. 1 = Enabled, Bit1 = Least Significant Bit. Bit 1: SSD Rate, 2: Priority, 3: Start, 4: Stop, 5: Double Coincidence, 6: Triple Coincidence, 7: Low TOF Decimation, 8: Alpha Decimation, 9: Proton Decimation, 10: Position A, 11: Position B.

Parameter.Name: SSD_ENABLES
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Bitmask for enabled SSD rates. 1 = Enabled, Bit1 = Least Significant Bit.

Parameter.Name: PRIORITY_ENABLES
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Bitmask for enabled Priority rates. 1 = Enabled, Bit1 = Least Significant Bit.

Parameter.Name: START_DIMENSIONS
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Number of E/q Steps and Number of Elevation Steps for Start Rate

Parameter.Name: STOP_DIMENSIONS
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Number of E/q Steps and Number of Elevation Steps for Stop Rate

Parameter.Name: DC_DIMENSIONS
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Number of E/q Steps and Number of Elevation Steps for Double Coincidence Rate

Parameter.Name: TC_DIMENSIONS
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Number of E/q Steps and Number of Elevation Steps for Triple Coincidence Rate

Parameter.Name: LOW_TOF_DIMENSIONS
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Number of E/q Steps and Number of Elevation Steps for Low TOF Rate

Parameter.Name: PROTON_DEC_DIMENSIONS
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Number of E/q Steps and Number of Elevation Steps for Proton Decimation Rate

Parameter.Name: ALPHA_DEC_DIMENSIONS
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Number of E/q Steps and Number of Elevation Steps for Alpha Decimation Rate

Parameter.Name: POS_A_DIMENSIONS
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Number of E/q Steps and Number of Elevation Steps for Position A Rate

Parameter.Name: POS_B_DIMENSIONS
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Number of E/q Steps and Number of Elevation Steps for Position B Rate

Parameter.Name: SSD_DIMENSIONS
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Number of SSDs and Number of E/q Steps and Number of Elevation Steps

Parameter.Name: PRIORITY_DIMENSIONS
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Number of Priority Ranges and Number of E/q Steps and Number of Elevation Steps

Parameter.Name: START_RATE
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Counts/sec on Start MCP detector. Dimensions are maximum possible sizes. Consult START_DIMENSIONS for actual sizes in data.

Parameter.Name: STOP_RATE
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Number of counts on Stop MCP detector. Dimensions are maximum possible sizes. Consult STOP_DIMENSIONS for actual sizes in data. When only one elevation step, DEPEND_2 should be ELEVATION_SUMMED.

Parameter.Name: DC_RATE
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Number of double coincidence events that have a start signal with a corresponding stop signal. Dimensions are maximum possible sizes. Consult DC_DIMENSIONS for actual sizes in data.

Parameter.Name: TC_RATE
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Number of triple coincidence events that have a start signal with a corresponding stop and energy signals. Dimensions are maximum possible sizes. Consult TC_DIMENSIONS for actual sizes in data.

Parameter.Name: LOWTOF_RATE
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Number of double coincidence events below low TOF threshold. Dimensions are maximum possible sizes. Consult LOW_TOF_DIMENSIONS for actual sizes in data.

Parameter.Name: PROTON_DEC_RATE
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Number of double coincidence events within proton TOF range. Dimensions are maximum possible sizes. Consult PROTON_DEC_DIMENSIONS for actual sizes in data.

Parameter.Name: ALPHA_DEC_RATE
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Number of double coincidence events within alpha TOF range. Dimensions are maximum possible sizes. Consult ALPHA_DEC_DIMENSIONS for actual sizes in data.

Parameter.Name: POS_A_RATE
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Counts/sec on Position A detector. Dimensions are maximum possible sizes. Consult START_DIMENSIONS for actual sizes in data.

Parameter.Name: POS_B_RATE
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Counts/sec on Position B detector. Dimensions are maximum possible sizes. Consult START_DIMENSIONS for actual sizes in data.

Parameter.Name: SSD_RATE
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Number of counts on each solid state detector. Dimensions are maximum possible sizes. Consult SSD_DIMENSIONS for actual sizes in data. SSDs 30 and 31 were not populated with physical detectors. In contrast, SSD 29 was disabled in software and will likely remain so. Any signals in these elements are due to electronic noise and not from real particles. When only one elevation step, DEPEND_2 should be ELEVATION_SUMMED.

Parameter.Name: PRIORITY_RATE
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Number of events in each priority range. 0: double coincidence PHAs (pickup ions), 1: Fe, 2: Mg, Si, S, 3: CNO (except O6+), 4: O6+, 5: Alphas, 6: Protons, 7: Error (low or unrealistically long TOFs). These are nominal categories and subject to change. Dimensions are maximum possible sizes. Consult PRIORITY_DIMENSIONS for actual sizes in data.

Parameter.Name: PRIORITY_VERSION
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Version number of the priority boundaries. These define the 8 priorities, numbered 1-7, used to prioritize which PHAs are downlinked.

Parameter.Name: SPECIES_BOX_VERSION
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Version number of the species boxes. These define 32 boxes in E/Q - TOF - E space which are set to the locations of counts for individual ion species.

Parameter.Name: SSD_THRESHOLD_VERSION
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Version number of the set of SSD thresholds (1 master and 30 trim) used to collect the data. These settings affect the sensitivity of HIS and the noise allowed into the onboard event processing through the SSD subsystem. Version numbers are given only to sets of values used for science data collection, not for testing.

Parameter.Name: PROD_CONF_TBL_NUM
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: Product configuration table number used during data collection. This table sets the dimensions of rate products produced onboard.

Parameter.Name: PA_HVPS_SET_POINT
Parameter.Set: Time series defined by using: EPOCH
Parameter.Caveats: This is the voltage setting for the PA HVPS, e.g. -10 kV, -25 kV. Note: It is not the reading of the on-board voltage monitor for this supply. Valid [0, -30 kV].

Parameter.Name: EOQ
Parameter.Caveats: E/q steps spanning the range 0.50 to 75.1 keV/e. Value is midpoint of step. Lower bound is EOQ value minus EOQ_DELTA, and upper bound is EOQ value plus EOQ_DELTA.

Parameter.Name: EOQ
Parameter.Caveats: Delta is from the midpoint in EOQ variable. Lower bound is EOQ value minus EOQ_DELTA, and upper bound is EOQ value plus EOQ_DELTA.

Parameter.Name: ELEVATION
Parameter.Caveats: The elevation range is nominally -20 to +16 deg, with +/-3 degree uncertainty. These values are subject to change after in-flight calibration. Value is the midpoint of the elevation bin. Lower bound is ELEVATION value minus ELEVATION_DELTA, and upper bound is ELEVATION value plus ELEVATION_DELTA. These values are only valid over a limited E/q range, 0-10 keV/e. These are based on current calibration, which may be updated in the future.

Parameter.Name: ELEVATION_DELTA
Parameter.Caveats: Delta is from the midpoint in ELEVATION variable. Lower bound is ELEVATION value minus ELEVATION_DELTA, and upper bound is ELEVATION value plus ELEVATION_DELTA. These values are only valid over a limited E/q range, 0-10 keV/e. These are based on current calibration, which may be updated in the future.

Parameter.Name: ELEVATION_SUMMED
Parameter.Description: Elevation step when summed to one bin
Parameter.Caveats: This variable is used when elevation is summed. The elevation range is nominally -20 to +16 deg, with +/-3 degree uncertainty. These values are subject to change after in-flight calibration. Value is the midpoint of the ELEVATION bin. Lower bound is ELEVATION value minus ELEVATION_DELTA, and upper bound is ELEVATION value plus ELEVATION_DELTA. Only the first element is used; all others are fill. These values are only valid over a limited E/q range, 0-10 keV/e. These are based on current calibration, which may be updated in the future.

Parameter.Name: ELEVATION_SUMMED_DELTA
Parameter.Description: Delta for elevation step when summed to one bin
Parameter.Caveats: Delta is from the midpoint in ELEVATION variable. Lower bound is ELEVATION value minus ELEVATION_DELTA, and upper bound is ELEVATION value plus ELEVATION_DELTA. Only the first element is used; all others are fill. These values are only valid over a limited E/q range, 0-10 keV/e. These are based on current calibration, which may be updated in the future.

Parameter.Name: AZIMUTH
Parameter.Caveats: The azimuth range is nominally -33 to +66 degrees, with +/- 3 degree uncertainty. These values are subject to change after in-flight calibration. Value is the midpoint of the azimuth bin. Lower bound is AZIMUTH value minus AZIMUTH_DELTA, and upper bound is AZIMUTH value plus AZIMUTH_DELTA.

Parameter.Name: AZIMUTH_DELTA
Parameter.Caveats: Delta is from the midpoint in the AZIMUTH variable. Lower bound is AZIMUTH value minus AZIMUTH_DELTA, and upper bound is AZIMUTH value plus AZIMUTH_DELTA.

Parameter.Name: PRIORITY
Parameter.Caveats: 0: double coincidence PHAs (pickup ions), 1: Fe, 2: Mg, Si, S, 3: O6+, 4: CNO (except O6+), 5: Alphas, 6: Protons, 7: Error (low or unrealistically long TOFs).
